It must be understood that these definitions hold only if mechanical strains are identical with total strains. For convenience, in calculating the averaged properties of the laminate by integration over the layers, the stress–strain relations are rearranged. The new vector l0 appears on the left side of the constitutive equations and contains the constant magnitudes only
(A.5)l0T={ɛx 0   ɛy 0   σz 0   τzy 0   τzx 0   γxy 0}
while vector rk appears on the right-hand side and contains only the magnitudes that may vary from layer to layer,
(A.6)rkT={σx k   σy k   ɛz k   γzy k   γzx k   τxy k}
